Search and rescue missions continue in Kwa-Zulu Natal, which was ravished by floods on Monday. The deadliest rains ever experienced in the province left more than 350 people dead. Gift of the Givers, which has been at the forefront helping destitute victims, said their team had responded to an urgent call on Friday, where a local bridge had collapsed into a home. The non profit organisation reported that the mother and her three children, who resided here, were unfortunately still missing. “Our team is currently conducting assessments in this area,” said the team in a statement. Also read: More aid comes in to assist KZN floods victims KZN floods death toll rises to 306 as mop-up operations begin Celebs come together to raise funds for those affected by KZN floods Follow @SundayWorldZA on Twitter @sundayworldza on Instagram, or like our Facebook Page, Sunday World, by clicking here for the latest breaking news in South Africa. To Subscribe to Sunday World, click here.